Overview
* PuzzleRPG is turn based smartphone roguelike
* Target audience are RPG fans in public transport, playing with 1 hand
* The game should have simple visuals but deep gameplay - nearly like MUDs of the past
* The goal of the game is to survive as long as possible in randomly generated world
* The gameplay is about collecting resources, crafting valuables and fighting enemies
* To survive, the character must fulfil primary needs (to eat, to sleep, etc)
* The difficulty escalates over time, so the only way to survive is to develop more and more advanced tools

Core gameplay
* The game world is presented as field of hexagons
* The character is prehistoric man
* Few first goals are to craft a weapon, to hunt a deer, to make a fire, to cook a food
* The game is turn based
* The character can spend a turn to move to adjasted hexagon, or to do a context dependent action on a current hexagon
* Possible actions on a hexagon are : collect, use and attack
* Collect is low priority action, executed when there is nothing to use or attack. Example: pick up a stone
* Use is medium priority action, executed on an object if there is nothing to attack. Example: use a fire to cook
* Attack is high priority action, executed on an enemy or prey in a hexagon
